{"id": "unknown-2026-04-23-002", "date": "2026-04-23", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 17, "weekday": "Thu"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["shipbuilding_orders"], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": []}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "Odfjell lines up four newbuilds in Japan", "content": "<p>Norwegian chemical tanker owner Odfjell is pressing ahead with its fleet renewal drive, securing four 40,000 dwt fully stainless-steel newbuildings from Japan. The Bergen-based group said it has agreed to acquire the vessels from a Japanese owner upon delivery from Kitanihon Shipbuilding, with handovers scheduled between the first quarter of 2027 and the second quarter &#8230;</p>\n</p>\n", "sources": []}
